Capparis decidua

    Authority   (Forsk.)
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Capparales:Capparidaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names Injet (Amargna), Maluza (Amargna), Yomonoxe (Amargna)
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 4145

   Notes
   SOURCES (C. decidua (Forsk.) Edgew.)
   Rashid M 1975 pp 144-147 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, PH, LIG, USE]
   IBPGR 1984 pp 41
   Yadav M (pers. comm.)
   KILLING T
   Resistant to below -5Â°C.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial shrub or small tree. Flowers appear in March-April and fruits
   ripen in May-June. Life span of 40-50 years.
   COMMON NAMES
   Kurrel, Karer, Ker, Kyaro, Kerdo, Kyarado, Kera, Kareel, Chippuri,
   Shiprigidda, Karil, Delha, Karir, Karira, Gudhapata, Sengam,
   Sanganchedi, Kariramu, Tundub, Tuntub, Meringa, Tenti, Dila.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: C. aphylla, Sodada decidua. Kurrel can reach a
   height of 7 m. Optimum yield is 20 kg per bush. The shrub can reach a
   height of 4.5-6 m.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
